```javascript
db.digitalContents.countDocuments({
  type: "series",
  companySectionIds: "908686",
  "scripts.title": { $regex: "Pier", $options: "i" }
})
```

The ID uniquely identifies the company section (the name is redundant identifying information given in the text, already implied by the ID), so filtering on `companySectionIds: "908686"` (Mongo matches if the array contains the value) plus `type: "series"` and a case-insensitive regex on any embedded script's `title` answers the request; `countDocuments` returns the count directly.

```javascript
PUT /locations
{
  "mappings": {
    "properties": {
      "id":          { "type": "keyword" },
      "name":        { "type": "text", "fields": { "keyword": { "type": "keyword" } } },
      "description": { "type": "text" },
      "furniture":   { "type": "text" },
      "indoor":      { "type": "boolean" }
    }
  }
}
```

`id` is a `keyword` (exact-match identifier, not analyzed). `name` gets a `text` field for full-text search plus a `.keyword` sub-field for exact match/aggregations. `description` and `furniture` are free text and must be analyzed `text` fields to support the relevance queries later in the exercise. `indoor` (Yes/No) maps naturally to a `boolean`.

```javascript
GET /locations/_search
{
  "query": {
    "bool": {
      "must": [
        { "match": { "description": "Stadium" } },
        { "match": { "description": "Basketball" } }
      ],
      "should": [
        { "match": { "furniture": "Planet" } },
        { "match": { "description": "Space" } }
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

The `must` clauses are mandatory (both "Stadium" and "Basketball" must appear in `description`), guaranteeing the document is returned; the `should` clauses are optional but contribute extra `_score` when "Planet" appears in `furniture` or "Space" in `description`, boosting the ranking of documents matching all four words without excluding the ones matching only the mandatory two.

```javascript
GET /locations/_search
{
  "size": 0,
  "aggs": {
    "by_indoor": {
      "terms": { "field": "indoor" }
    }
  }
}
```

`size: 0` avoids returning the matched documents themselves — we only want the aggregation. A `terms` aggregation on the `indoor` boolean field buckets and counts documents into `true` (indoor) and `false` (outdoor) groups, giving both counts in one query.
